ance","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Marguerite","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Margaret  , also used in the English-speaking world, where its use has been reinforced by the fact that the name was adopted in the 19th century for a garden flower, a large cultivated variety of daisy. <i>Margaret</i> was earlier used in English as a dialect word denoting the ox-eye daisy, and the French equivalent was borrowed into English just in time to catch the vogue for deriving girls' names from vocabulary words denoting flowers.  See also  Daisy ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Marguerite d'Aulnay was born about 1300, in Naples, Kingdom of Naples, her father, Robert d'Aulnay, was 26 and her mother, Isabella Stendardo, was 21. She married Conte di Andria e di Montescaglioso Bertrand III des Baux in 1320. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died about 1350, in her hometown, at the age of 52, and was buried in Naples, Kingdom of Naples."},"et":{"about 1300–about 1350":"umbes 1300–umbes 1350","1300–1350":"1300–1350","1295–1347":"1295–1347","1327–1414":"1327–1414","1330–1422":"1330–1422","1275–1319":"1275–1319","1280–1355":"1280–1355","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","1295":"1295","1350":"1350","15 September 1347":"15. september 1347","1280":"1280","Abt 1327":"umbes 1327","1327":"1327","1414":"1414","1347":"1347","1422":"1422","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1320":"1320","about 1300":"umbes 1300","1319":"1319","about 1350":"umbes 1350","Naples, Italy":"Napoli, Regno di Napoli","Andria, Bari, Italy":"Andria, Bari, Puglia, Itaalia","Arcadia, Peloponnese, Greece":"Arcadia, Pelopónnisos, Kreeka","Naples, Kingdom of Naples":"Napoli, Regno di Napoli","Deville, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Deville, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1300–about 1350":"noin 1300–noin 1350","1300–1350":"1300–1350","1295–1347":"1295–1347","1327–1414":"1327–1414","13